version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-01-17"
keywords:
  - coalition formation
  - large language models
  - game theory
  - multi-agent systems
  - Nash stability
  - hedonic games
abstract: >-
  The first formal framework for analyzing coalition formation dynamics 
  in LLM agent networks, grounded in hedonic game theory. We introduce 
  the LLM Coalition Formation Game (LCFG), establish sufficient conditions 
  for Nash-stable partitions, prove complexity bounds for stability verification, 
  and introduce Coalition-of-Thought (CoalT), a prompting protocol achieving 
  73.2% Nash stability (+14.8pp over vanilla CoT).
